Description: Joseph organising the harvest of grain in Egypt; Joseph standing on the right giving instructions to three farmers in the middle and left; cut image of three women wearing hats on verso; illustration to an edition of the Dutch "Biblia Sacra" (Jan van Moerentorf: 1645). c.1645 Woodcut
Producer name: Print made by: Christoffel van Sichem III
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of book-illustrations by Christoffel van Sichem III, see 1895,0420.176.1-93.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (49)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Augustus Wollaston Franks
